```typescript
armature.animation.setMovementEventCallFunc(
    callback: (armature: ccs.Armature, movementType: number, movementID: string) => void
): void
```

The callback receives:
- `armature: ccs.Armature` — the armature that owns this animation
- `movementType: number` — the event type, one of:
  - `ccs.MovementEventType.START`
  - `ccs.MovementEventType.COMPLETE`
  - `ccs.MovementEventType.LOOP_COMPLETE`
- `movementID: string` — the name of the animation movement

Example with typed callback:
```typescript
const onMovement = (arm: ccs.Armature, type: number, id: string): void => {
    if (type === ccs.MovementEventType.COMPLETE) {
        cc.log('Finished:', id);
    }
};

armature.animation.setMovementEventCallFunc(onMovement);
```

```typescript
armature.animation.setFrameEventCallFunc(
    callback: (bone: ccs.Bone, frameEventName: string, originFrameIndex: number, currentFrameIndex: number) => void
